related_questions.question: Where does solar power get its energy from?
related_questions.snippet: Solar-powered photovoltaic (PV) panels convert the sun's rays into electricity by exciting electrons in silicon cells using the photons of light from the sun. This electricity can then be used to supply renewable energy to your home or business.

related_questions.question: What are the most common photovoltaic cells used today?
related_questions.snippet: Crystalline silicon modules are the most extensively studied PV type in terms of LCA since they are the most commonly used. Mono-crystalline silicon photovoltaic systems (mono-si) have an average efficiency of 14.0%.

related_questions.question: Which is the largest solar power plant in India?
related_questions.snippet: Kamuthi Solar Power Project is the largest single location solar power plant in the world, located at Kamuthi in Tamil Nadu. The Kamuthi solar plant is the world's second largest solar park with a capacity of 648 MW commissioned by Adani Power.
